{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4784-library-new-request-io.projectreactor.tools-blockhound-1.0.8.RELEASE-ba5dcc80\n\nMost likely this failed in the test-generation/native-validation loop, not coverage discovery. Dynamic-access coverage still reached 221/235 (94.04%), but the run metrics ended with no publishable artifacts (`generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`) and the starting/ending commit both stayed at `0eb0c21f765ed9a298b5fc3f110157450f23930b`. The preserved test tree also did not converge to a library-specific BlockHound test: `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/BlockhoundTest.java` is still a placeholder.\n\nThe latest validation logs show unresolved native-image gaps. `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-10T19-56-47-142724Z.log` ends with 4 native test failures (`ClassReaderTest`, `TypePoolInnerClassLoadingTest`, `ConstantsTest`, `SerializedConstantTest`). `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-10T20-00-33-263003Z.log` prints “This is just a placeholder, implement your test” and then hits a `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassReaderTest.class`. `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-10T20-00-28-596647Z.log` also shows `generateMetadata` failing because `libnative-image-agent.so` could not be found, so the fix loop could not regenerate metadata. There is partial follow-up work in `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/metadata-fix/codex.log`, but it did not finish the library.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-10T19-56-47-126255Z.log`\n- `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-10T19-56-47-142724Z.log`\n- `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-10T20-00-28-596647Z.log`\n- `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-10T20-00-33-263003Z.log`\n- `logs/io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Replace the placeholder/scaffold with a real BlockHound-specific test that exercises supported BlockHound behavior, not just shaded Byte Buddy internals.\n2. Re-run `generateMetadata` and `test` in a GraalVM environment where `native-image-agent` is available, then add the missing resource/reflection registrations surfaced by the native logs.\n3. Validate the preserved branch with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.projectreactor.tools:blockhound:1.0.8.RELEASE` before resubmitting."}}
